Whoopie Pies
  --Cook's Country

Cakes:
2 c ap flour
1/2 c dutch processed cocoa powder
1 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp salt
1 c packed light brown sugar
8 tbsp (1 stick) unsalted butter softened but still cool
1 large egg, room temp
1 tsp vanilla
1 c buttermilk

Adjust oven racks to upper middle and lower middle positions and heat to 250F. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper. Whisk flour, cocoa, baking soda, and salt in medium bowl. With electric mixer on medium speed, beat sugar, and butter in large bowl until fluffy, ~4 min. Beat in egg until incorporated, scraping down sides of bowl as necessary, then beat in vanilla. Reduce speed to low and beat in 1/3 of flour mixture, then half buttermilk. Repeat with half of remaining flour mixture, then remainign buttermilk, and finally, remaining flour mixture. Using rubber spatula, give batter final stir. Using 1/3 c measure, scoop 6 mounds of batter onto each baking sheet, spacing mounds ~3" apart. Bake until cakes spring back when pressed, 15-18 min, switching and rotating pans halfway through baking. Cool completely on baking sheets, at least 1 hr.

Filling:
12 tbsp (1 1/2 sticks) unsalted butter softened but still cook
1 1/4 c confectioners' sugar
1 1/2 tsp vanilla
1/8 tsp salt
2 1/2 c marshmallow fluff

With electric mixer on medium speed, beat butter and sugar together until fluffy, ~2 min. Beat in vanilla and salt. Beat in fluff until incorporated, ~2 min. Refrigerate filling until slightly firm, ~30 min. Bowl can be wrapped and refrigerated for up to 2 days. Dollop 1/3 filling on center of flat side of 6 cakes. Top with flat side of remaining 6 cakes and gently press until filling spreads to edge of cake. Serve. Can refrigerate in airtight container up to 3 days.
